<subSubSection id="5A189F6FFC13385676F67ABD52FBDAA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="BC9F3229A3EBB3B30A9A515F317020DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D72E6B055C4295FE3AC0912710B8972" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<normalizedToken id="CE5E40EB8A6BAA2DA5C50A3155C5CDD0" originalValue="Α">Α</normalizedToken>
new subspecies for the Greek flora. 
<taxonomicName id="A5C030399009746272E12189680FB1F8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="matronalis">
<emphasis id="347D2F2E5A17565C5267349703B94F6C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Hesperis matronalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widespread and variable species divided into 6 or 7 subspecies, of which subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="AB39B97C0BCB5C326638FA881AC2853D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis subsp. cladotricha" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="matronalis" subSpecies="cladotricha">Hesperis matronalis cladotricha</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken id="5E8099CE11937AD4768D8768D967DD2B" originalValue="Borbás">Borbas</normalizedToken>
) Hayek has been recorded as a rare plant of the Mt. Timfi area in north-west Greece (
<bibRefCitation id="9B9DACF62C5CB3BE8549D9F5467E4036" author="Goulimis, C. N." journalOrPublisher="Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668186" refString="Goulimis, C. N., 1960. New additions to the Greek flora. Second series. Athens" title="New additions to the Greek flora. Second series" year="1960">Goulimis 1960</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="1962E1E04028AABD51889C54170A3D02" author="Ganiatsas, K." journalOrPublisher="lpirotiki Estia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="251 - 275" refId="B7668156" refString="Ganiatsas, K., 1971. Botanical studies in the Vikos Ravine. lpirotiki Estia 228, 229, 230: 251 - 275" title="Botanical studies in the Vikos Ravine" volume="228, 229, 230" year="1971">Ganiatsas 1971</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="5054A647260730CE7CA916A822C281A1" author="Authier, P." journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Gallica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="525 - 533" refId="B7667767" refString="Authier, P., 1993. Contributions a &quot;Flora hellenica&quot;: la flore de la region des Monts Timfi (Epire, nord-ouest Grece) (I). Acta Botanica Gallica 140 (5): 525 - 533" title="Contributions a &quot; Flora hellenica &quot;: la flore de la region des Monts Timfi (Epire, nord-ouest Grece) (I)" volume="140" year="1993">Authier 1993</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E38079516926EB96448C86A62DB1AB42" author="Bergmeier, E." journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia, 38 (2): 465 - 474" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667845" refString="Bergmeier, E., 2008. Med-Checklist Notulae 27. Willdenowia, 38 (2): 465-474" title="Med-Checklist Notulae 27" year="2008">Bergmeier 2008</bibRefCitation>
). Our collection from NE Greece (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="407AF4E374F1322AF93F96E0579F9690" captionStartId="F7677624" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">13</figureCitation>
) presents a monomorphic indumentum on upper and lower leaf surfaces consisting of simple eglandular hairs; branched hairs are very scarce and rarely found along veins and margins. It clearly fits subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="C6424DD1F04FA8CEDB271FDC812D7D60" authority="matronalis" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis subsp. matronalis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="matronalis" subSpecies="matronalis">Hesperis matronalis matronalis</taxonomicName>
because of its unbranched hairs, pink-purple flowers and petiolate middle and upper stem leaves. In contrast, a specimen of subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="C465EC6EDCD2BDAC932DB70255E681EC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis subsp. cladotricha" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="matronalis" subSpecies="cladotricha">Hesperis matronalis cladotricha</taxonomicName>
examined (
<emphasis id="5D09A44A49F4C1996902497A5054C102" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
Κ. Goula &amp; 
<normalizedToken id="B54F9CDB6909D697054F68CD91E6A0F0" originalValue="Ν">Ν</normalizedToken>
.Α. Katsaros 3036
</emphasis>
, Mt Timfi, Skamneli, ATHU!) presents an indumentum of predominantly bifurcate (and occasionally trifurcate) eglandular hairs; simple hairs are very rare or absent. 
<taxonomicName id="9B167A1BE24A1FEFA84E554907D1EBF4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="matronalis">
<emphasis id="911BC8F052F74565D114489591FBF173" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Hesperis matronalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is present in all the floristic regions of neighbouring Bulgaria (
<bibRefCitation id="AFAAF6FEAF0DFC67B16AFDFE1F0C0471" author="Assyov, B." journalOrPublisher="Bulgarian Biodiversity Foundation, Sofia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667759" refString="Assyov, B., Petrova, A., 2012. Conspectus of the Bulgarian vascular flora (4rth edition). Bulgarian Biodiversity Foundation, Sofia" title="Conspectus of the Bulgarian vascular flora (4 rth edition)" year="2012">Assyov and Petrova 2012</bibRefCitation>
) and, therefore, its occurrence in NE Greece was to be expected. The Greek population grows in a very natural habitat away of any human interference and is clearly indigenous. Interestingly, a Greek collection of subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="4241A6F027E9AFAE02421F1AD7BA6645" authority="matronalis" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hesperis matronalis subsp. matronalis" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="matronalis" subSpecies="matronalis">Hesperis matronalis matronalis</taxonomicName>
already appeared amongst the specimens examined by 
<bibRefCitation id="2BA00E513B84397C0A3CFA15DE82B6F2" author="Duran, A." journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="239 - 247" refId="B7668084" refString="Duran, A., Ocak, A., 2005. Hesperis turkmendaghensis (sect. Hesperis (Cruciferae / Brassicaceae), a new species from the Central Anatolia region, Turkey. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 147: 239 - 247" title="Hesperis turkmendaghensis (sect. Hesperis (Cruciferae / Brassicaceae), a new species from the Central Anatolia region, Turkey" volume="147" year="2005">Duran and Ocak (2005)</bibRefCitation>
from Mt. Pangeo (Pangaeo, west of Kawala, 
